on your mind.

777
00:59:11,077 --> 00:59:12,949
I wish you'd tell me.

778
00:59:13,078 --> 00:59:14,452
I really do.

779
00:59:14,579 --> 00:59:17,412
I wish that you'd feel
that you could talk to me...

780
00:59:17,538 --> 00:59:19,908
and that we
could be friends.

781
00:59:20,038 --> 00:59:23,736
I mean aside from
all of this junk.

782
00:59:45,878 --> 00:59:48,202
Would you, um...

783
00:59:48,338 --> 00:59:52,414
If you were a girl who'd
waited for someone...

784
01:00:00,049 --> 01:00:03,663
You can trust me.

785
01:00:06,550 --> 01:00:09,418
Well, you never
really knew...

786
01:00:09,550 --> 01:00:12,419
when he was going to
come to see you.

787
01:00:12,551 --> 01:00:14,922
You just lived
in a room alone...

788
01:00:15,053 --> 01:00:17,339
and you knew
nothing about him.

789
01:00:17,470 --> 01:00:19,342
And if you loved him...

790
01:00:19,470 --> 01:00:21,342
and were
patient with him...

791
01:00:21,470 --> 01:00:24,338
and even though
he didn't dare ever...

792
01:00:24,471 --> 01:00:27,837
tell you anything
about himself personally...

793
01:00:29,973 --> 01:00:32,343
Even though he may
have loved you...

794
01:00:32,474 --> 01:00:34,346
would you...

795
01:00:34,474 --> 01:00:36,844
Would I what?

796
01:00:36,974 --> 01:00:38,349
Would you...

797
01:00:39,975 --> 01:00:42,511
Would you
go back to him?

798
01:00:47,477 --> 01:00:49,349
Well, how would I know...

799
01:00:49,478 --> 01:00:52,761
How would I know
that he loved me?

800
01:01:00,480 --> 01:01:03,349
You'd have
no way of knowing.

801
01:01:15,901 --> 01:01:17,276
Hey, Harry!

802
01:01:17,402 --> 01:01:20,768
Did you hear the one about
the broad who busted Vegas?

803
01:01:20,902 --> 01:01:22,810
She wore
a see-through blouse.

804
01:01:46,909 --> 01:01:49,279
Where are
you going?

805
01:01:49,410 --> 01:01:52,195
Hey! Hey!

806
01:02:21,876 --> 01:02:24,365
You know something,
Harry?

807
01:02:24,502 --> 01:02:27,251
12 years ago, I recorded
every telephone call...

808
01:02:27,377 --> 01:02:29,250
made by the
presidential nominee...

809
01:02:29,379 --> 01:02:31,251
of a major
political party.

810
01:02:31,379 --> 01:02:32,753
I don't want to say
which party.

811
01:02:32,879 --> 01:02:35,250
Everywhere he went,
that's where I was.

812
01:02:35,380 --> 01:02:37,122
Coast to coast,
I was listening.

813
01:02:37,255 --> 01:02:39,127
I'm not saying I elected...

814
01:02:39,255 --> 01:02:41,709
the president of
the United States...

815
01:02:41,839 --> 01:02:44,127
but you can draw
your own conclusions.

816
01:02:44,257 --> 01:02:46,746
I mean, he lost.

817
01:02:46,883 --> 01:02:48,755
Harry, tell them
about the time...

818
01:02:48,883 --> 01:02:50,838
you put the bug
in the parakeet.

819
01:02:50,967 --> 01:02:51,832
Parakeet?

820
01:02:51,967 --> 01:02:53,294
No kidding.

821
01:02:53,425 --> 01:02:56,294
Harry one time actually
put a microphone...

822
01:02:56,426 --> 01:02:57,801
in a little
parakeet.

823
01:02:57,927 --> 01:02:59,301
Is that right?

824
01:02:59,427 --> 01:03:01,751
Parakeets don't happen
to be my thing...

825
01:03:01,887 --> 01:03:04,257
but I sure would
like to know...

826
01:03:04,387 --> 01:03:07,256
how you did
the teamster local back in '68.

827
01:03:07,388 --> 01:03:08,762
What was that?

828
01:03:08,888 --> 01:03:11,756
Don't you get papers
in Chicago, Millard?

829
01:03:11,889 --> 01:03:13,264
Probably
out on strike.

830
01:03:13,390 --> 01:03:15,676
It was all over
the front pages.

831
01:03:15,807 --> 01:03:18,177
Harry was working
for the attorney general.

832
01:03:18,307 --> 01:03:21,176
You didn't know
I knew, did you?

833
01:03:21,308 --> 01:03:23,678
The president of
this teamster local...

834
01:03:23,808 --> 01:03:26,179
set up a phony
welfare fund.

835
01:03:26,309 --> 01:03:29,676
I mean, you correct me
on the details, Harry.

836
01:03:29,810 --> 01:03:32,180
I may be
a little fuzzy.

837
01:03:32,310 --> 01:03:34,183
Only two people
seemed to know...

838
01:03:34,312 --> 01:03:36,184
the president
and his accountant.

839
01:03:36,312 --> 01:03:38,599
They only talked about it
on fishing trips.

840
01:03:38,729 --> 01:03:40,104
On a private boat...

841
01:03:40,230 --> 01:03:42,683
That was the only place
they talked details.

842
01:03:42,814 --> 01:03:44,851
That boat was bug-proof.
That's a fact.

843
01:03:44,981 --> 01:03:47,351
They wouldn't strike up
a conversation...

844
01:03:47,481 --> 01:03:50,349
if there was another boat
on the horizon.

845
01:03:50,482 --> 01:03:52,853
That didn't stop Harry,
did it?

846
01:03:52,982 --> 01:03:54,357
No, he recorded
everything.

847
01:03:54,483 --> 01:03:56,189
Nobody knows
how you did it though.

848
01:03:56,317 --> 01:03:58,190
Caused a hell of
a scandal.

849
01:03:58,318 --> 01:03:59,561
Why?

850
01:03:59,693 --> 01:04:02,182
No reason.
Three people were murdered.

851
01:04:02,318 --> 01:04:06,479
Harry's a bit too modest
to tell us how he did it.

852
01:04:09,320 --> 01:04:11,192
It had nothing
to do with me.

853
01:04:11,320 --> 01:04:13,692
I just turned in
the tapes.

854
01:04:13,821 --> 01:04:16,145
The president thought
the accountant talked.

855
01:04:16,281 --> 01:04:18,153
Nobody really
knows for sure.

856
01:04:18,281 --> 01:04:19,656
Three days later...

857
01:04:19,782 --> 01:04:22,650
they found the accountant,
his wife, and kid...

858
01:04:22,782 --> 01:04:25,651
naked and tied up
in the house...

859
01:04:25,782 --> 01:04:28,652
Hands and feet
tied up with rope...

860
01:04:28,783 --> 01:04:31,154
all the hair on their bodies
shaved off.

861
01:04:31,285 --> 01:04:33,655
The heads were found
in different places.

862
01:04:33,785 --> 01:04:35,159
They killed them?

863
01:04:35,285 --> 01:04:36,660
No. They
gift-wrapped them.

864
01:04:36,786 --> 01:04:38,658
This is
ancient history now.

865
01:04:38,786 --> 01:04:40,161
Harry, how'd you do it?

866
01:04:40,287 --> 01:04:43,653
What they do with the tapes
is their business.

867
01:04:43,787 --> 01:04:47,652
Next thing I knew,
you moved out of New York.

868
01:04:47,788 --> 01:04:50,159
It had nothing
to do with me.

869
01:04:50,289 --> 01:04:52,659
Come on, show and tell.
How'd you do it?

870
01:04:52,789 --> 01:04:54,828
For God's sake,
tell him.

871
01:04:59,791 --> 01:05:01,166
Turn it off, Stan.

872
01:05:01,292 --> 01:05:02,489
What for?

873
01:05:02,625 --> 01:05:04,830
Stan, turn it off.

874
01:05:04,959 --> 01:05:06,998
They ought to hear this.

875
01:05:07,127 --> 01:05:09,165
It's the best thing
you've ever done.

876
01:05:12,795 --> 01:05:15,082
What was that, Stan?

877
01:05:16,921 --> 01:05:21,580
Well, it's the assignment
that Harry did this week.

878
01:05:21,714 --> 01:05:23,088
It'll make history.

879
01:05:23,214 --> 01:05:24,589
Yeah?

880
01:05:24,715 --> 01:05:28,081
There's no moment between
human beings that I cannot record...

881
01:05:28,216 --> 01:05:31,747
and there's no method
that I cannot figure out.

882
01:05:31,883 --> 01:05:34,751
I could figure out
any of Harry's schemes, right?

883
01:05:34,884 --> 01:05:37,503
Come on, come on.
Try me.

884
01:05:37,634 --> 01:05:40,503
Let me give him
the assignment, Harry.

885
01:05:40,635 --> 01:05:42,792
Yeah.

886
01:05:47,804 --> 01:05:51,170
This is a quad
in the center of the city.

887
01:05:51,305 --> 01:05:53,675
These are steps,
benches all around.

888
01:05:53,805 --> 01:05:55,180
It's 12:00 noon...

889
01:05:55,305 --> 01:05:57,178
which means
that it's lunchtime...

890
01:05:57,306 --> 01:06:00,175
for the people working
in these offices.

891
01:06:00,307 --> 01:06:02,179
They're walking, talking,
having lunch...

892
01:06:02,307 --> 01:06:03,682
and it's crowded.

893
01:06:03,808 --> 01:06:05,182
Naturally.
Come on, Stan.

894
01:06:05,308 --> 01:06:08,177
Okay. Two people are constantly
moving in circles...

895
01:06:08,309 --> 01:06:10,181
in and out
of the crowd.

896
01:06:10,309 --> 01:06:12,881
We don't know whether
they'll sit down or what.

897
01:06:12,977 --> 01:06:15,182
They're convinced
they can't be recorded...

898
01:06:15,311 --> 01:06:18,678
because they're in a crowd
and constantly moving.

899
01:06:18,812 --> 01:06:20,186
Yet, they're the target.

900
01:06:20,312 --> 01:06:22,599
The assignment is
to get everything they say.

901
01:06:22,729 --> 01:06:24,686
How would you do it?

902
01:06:24,814 --> 01:06:26,686
One system
won't do it.

903
01:06:26,814 --> 01:06:28,686
I could've
told you that.

904
01:06:28,814 --> 01:06:30,189
Why didn't you?

905
01:06:30,315 --> 01:06:32,187
Go on,
figure it out.

906
01:06:32,315 --> 01:06:34,105
You get to
their clothes first.

907
01:06:34,232 --> 01:06:35,607
You pre-rig
their clothes.

908
01:06:35,733 --> 01:06:37,605
There's no way
of telling...

909
01:06:37,733 --> 01:06:39,013
what they're
going to be wearing.

910
01:06:39,151 --> 01:06:41,521
Get somebody to
bump into them.

911
01:06:41,651 --> 01:06:44,934
Get a drunk to plant
a pin mike on them.

912
01:06:45,069 --> 01:06:47,225
They've been bugged before.
It's too risky.

913
01:06:47,361 --> 01:06:48,605
I got it.

914
01:06:49,819 --> 01:06:52,604
You hire a lip-reader
with binoculars.

915
01:06:52,737 --> 01:06:55,605
No. The client wants
their actual voice.

916
01:06:55,738 --> 01:06:57,611
Why?

917
01:06:57,739 --> 01:06:59,528
So he can
believe it.

918
01:06:59,656 --> 01:07:02,026
All right.
I'll figure it out.

919
01:07:02,156 --> 01:07:05,108
I don't know.
It must've been an expensive show.

920
01:07:05,240 --> 01:07:06,615
Who was so interested?

921
01:07:06,741 --> 01:07:08,115
Yeah, was it us?

922
01:07:08,241 --> 01:07:09,106
Who's us?

923
01:07:09,242 --> 01:07:10,106
Federal government.

924
01:07:10,241 --> 01:07:11,106
Private party.

925
01:07:11,242 --> 01:07:14,110
It would take
at least four passes.

926
01:07:14,243 --> 01:07:16,115
I did it in three.

927
01:07:16,243 --> 01:07:19,111
Three? That's very nice.
What did you use?

928
01:07:19,243 --> 01:07:20,618
Three-stage directional
microphones...

929
01:07:20,744 --> 01:07:23,613
with Mosfet amplifier
of my own design.

930
01:07:23,745 --> 01:07:26,614
We got another 20% conventionally
just tailing them.

931
01:07:26,746 --> 01:07:27,611
Paul did.

932
01:07:27,746 --> 01:07:30,532
It was beautiful.
It really was.

933
01:07:30,663 --> 01:07:33,034
It was
a work of art.

934
01:07:33,164 --> 01:07:35,535
You should have
seen it, though.

935
01:07:35,665 --> 01:07:37,122
These new microphones
are just incredible.

936
01:07:37,248 --> 01:07:39,039
I couldn't believe it
myself.

937
01:07:39,166 --> 01:07:41,038
We were 200 yards away.

938
01:07:41,166 --> 01:07:42,541
It was absolutely
readable.

939
01:07:42,666 --> 01:07:44,788
I broke in a couple
of newsreel cameramen.

940
01:07:44,917 --> 01:07:46,291
You should have
been there, Bernie.

941
01:07:46,417 --> 01:07:47,697
What did they do?

942
01:07:47,835 --> 01:07:50,122
They took the cross hairs
of the telescope...

943
01:07:50,252 --> 01:07:52,622
and lined it up
on the mouths...

944
01:07:52,752 --> 01:07:55,621
No. The boy and the girl.
What did they do?

945
01:07:55,753 --> 01:07:57,128
Oh, I don't know.

946
01:07:57,254 --> 01:07:59,624
But it was beautiful,
something to see.

947
01:07:59,754 --> 01:08:01,128
Yeah.
Sounds very pretty.

948
01:08:01,254 --> 01:08:04,123
I'd like to take
a look at that mike, too.

949
01:08:04,255 --> 01:08:05,630
There it is.

950
01:08:05,756 --> 01:08:07,130
Oh.

951
01:08:07,256 --> 01:08:10,373
I always said
we should be partners, Harry.

952
01:08:10,507 --> 01:08:14,123
You're the best, but you
and me together, that'd be tops.

953
01:08:14,258 --> 01:08:18,039
I need a quick look at
your plans and devices.

954
01:08:18,176 --> 01:08:20,083
I got all the
manufacturing plants.

955
01:08:20,218 --> 01:08:23,051
We could make a fortune
selling to Uncle Sam.

956
01:08:23,177 --> 01:08:26,045
Did you hear about
the fag wiretapper...

957
01:08:26,178 --> 01:08:29,046
who could only tap
a Princess phone?

958
01:08:29,178 --> 01:08:30,092
No.

959
01:08:33,679 --> 01:08:35,552
Made that up
yourself, huh?

960
01:08:35,680 --> 01:08:38,051
It's pretty funny.

961
01:08:38,181 --> 01:08:39,555
Can I cut in?

962
01:08:39,681 --> 01:08:42,549
He's got a hell
of a sense of humor.

963
01:08:42,681 --> 01:08:44,554
I'm talking about
making millions...

964
01:08:44,683 --> 01:08:46,555
he's making
with the jokes.

965
01:08:46,683 --> 01:08:47,548
Come on!

966
01:08:47,683 --> 01:08:49,057
Thanks a lot.

967
01:08:49,183 --> 01:08:51,056
What do you say,
Harry?

968
01:08:51,185 --> 01:08:53,555
How about going
into a partnership?

969
01:08:53,685 --> 01:08:56,553
I could use a partner,
so could you.

970
01:08:56,686 --> 01:08:58,059
50-50, how about it?

971
01:08:58,186 --> 01:08:59,893
I don't need
anyone.

972
01:09:00,020 --> 01:09:01,394
That's all right.

973
01:09:01,520 --> 01:09:04,388
I do pretty good
on my own, anyway.

974
01:09:04,521 --> 01:09:07,887
You got to give credit
where credit's due, right?

975
01:09:08,022 --> 01:09:08,887
Abracadabra, Harry.

976
01:09:09,022 --> 01:09:10,894
See, I'm number two,
Harry.

977
01:09:11,023 --> 01:09:12,895
I have to try harder.

978
01:09:13,023 --> 01:09:16,021
<i>Would you, um...
If you were a girl...</i>

979
01:09:16,149 --> 01:09:17,523
<i>who'd waited
for someone...</i>

980
01:09:17,649 --> 01:09:19,023
<i>You can trust me.</i>

981
01:09:19,149 --> 01:09:22,516
Harry, that's you and me
when we were out there.

982
01:09:22,650 --> 01:09:24,522
What? No shit.
Ha ha ha.

983
01:09:24,651 --> 01:09:28,017
It's the Moran Super P-7
pen mike and transmitter.

984
01:09:28,152 --> 01:09:29,314
That's terrific!

985
01:09:29,444 --> 01:09:31,316
The bugger
got bugged, huh?

986
01:09:31,444 --> 01:09:32,819
He got you,
Harry.

987
01:09:32,944 --> 01:09:35,814
<i>And if you loved him
and were patient with him...</i>

988
01:09:35,945 --> 01:09:39,027
<i>and even though
he didn't dare ever...</i>

989
01:09:39,154 --> 01:09:42,319
<i>tell you anything about
himself personally...</i>

990
01:09:42,447 --> 01:09:43,822
Hey, touch, Harry.

991
01:09:43,948 --> 01:09:46,318
That's wild.
When did you do that?

992
01:09:46,448 --> 01:09:50,313
How do you like it?
What do you think?

993
01:09:50,450 --> 01:09:55,404
<i>Would you...
Would you go back to him?</i>

994
01:09:55,534 --> 01:09:58,616
I think you better
turn it off and get out.

995
01:09:58,743 --> 01:10:02,608
Are you kidding? It's just
a joke, for Christ's sakes.

996
01:10:02,744 --> 01:10:06,110
Bernie, Harry don't like you
to say "Christ's sakes."

997
01:10:06,244 --> 01:10:09,576
Well, I'm sorry, Harry.
Are you crazy, too, Stanley?

998
01:10:09,704 --> 01:10:10,569
What's wrong?

999
01:10:10,704 --> 01:10:12,576
Let's have
a party here.

1000
01:10:12,705 --> 01:10:14,079
Paul,
it's getting late.

1001
01:10:14,206 --> 01:10:15,912
Come on,
take it easy.

1002
01:10:16,039 --> 01:10:16,904
Come on.

1003
01:10:17,040 --> 01:10:17,904
Hey, Millard.

1004
01:10:18,039 --> 01:10:19,912
Know what
these things cost?

1005
01:10:20,040 --> 01:10:21,414
This cost 1,500 beans.

1006
01:10:21,540 --> 01:10:23,413
On the house,
from me to you.

1007
01:10:26,042 --> 01:10:27,997
Very nice to meet you.

1008
01:10:30,001 --> 01:10:31,459
It's only a joke.

1009
01:10:31,585 --> 01:10:32,959
Meredith?

1010
01:10:33,085 --> 01:10:34,459
He's got no sense
of humor.

1011
01:10:34,586 --> 01:10:36,956
No. I'm going to
stay here.

1012
01:10:37,086 --> 01:10:37,999
Paul!

1013
01:10:39,587 --> 01:10:40,831
Okay.

1014
01:10:44,088 --> 01:10:45,664
I forgot my bag.

1015
01:10:47,922 --> 01:10:49,297
Harry, I'm
really sorry.

1016
01:10:49,423 --> 01:10:50,963
I didn't mean
anything.

1017
01:10:51,089 --> 01:10:52,464
Come on, Stan.

1018
01:10:52,590 --> 01:10:54,462
See you Monday, Harry.

1019
01:10:54,590 --> 01:10:57,542
You want us to
put the lights out?

1020
01:11:16,555 --> 01:11:17,419
Night, Harry!

1021
01:11:17,554 --> 01:11:19,925
Yeah.
Goodnight, Harry.

1022
01:11:24,890 --> 01:11:26,265
<i>What do you think?</i>

1023
01:11:26,390 --> 01:11:29,259
<i>I don't know what
I'm going to get him...</i>

1024
01:11:29,391 --> 01:11:30,421
<i>for Christmas yet.</i>

1025
01:11:30,558 --> 01:11:31,933
<i>He's already
got everything.</i>

1026
01:11:38,060 --> 01:11:41,924
Harry, are you going to give me
a hard time tonight?

1027
01:11:43,645 --> 01:11:45,019
Harry!

1028
01:11:45,145 --> 01:11:46,425
Harry!

1029
01:11:46,562 --> 01:11:47,936
Come on.
Come back.

1030
01:11:48,062 --> 01:11:49,935
Turn it off.

1031
01:12:03,566 --> 01:12:05,107
She's frightened.

1032
01:12:05,233 --> 01:12:06,940
This is where
she's frightened.

1033
01:12:07,068 --> 01:12:09,438
